t distant galaxies of all could possibly produce dust at such early times, we‚Äôve finally learned that ‚Äútoo much, too soon,‚Äù is the wrong question to be asking. Apparently, the recipe our own galaxy uses wasn‚Äôt the recipe the Universe followed back in its more pristine past! This article Cosmic dust: ‚Äútoo much, too soon‚Äù no longer! is featured on Big Think .␀␀␀␀␀—R␀␀␀␀␀Cosmic dust: ‚Äútoo much, too soon‚Äù no longer!

